&gt; &gt; Is there some way to form a query to the DNS such that, given a network
&gt; &gt; number (not a host address), I can get back the name of the network?
&gt; &gt; (e.g. I have 128.32 and I want back "ucb-ether")....

	
&gt; I thought there was an IETF Working Group (domains?) chartered to take
&gt; care of this?  I recall discussion of it at Annapolis, I believe.

Bob,

The IETF Domain group is inactive at this time, in part due to the feeling
that their previously stated mission was complete.  However, I believe 
raising up a new group to attack other issues is entirely appropriate.  

So let me put a question to the namedroppers mailing list -- would there 
be interest in joining a working group under the IETF to address this (and 
other) DNS issues?  

Those wishing to suggest a chair for such a group may do so in separate 
mail to me.  Thanks.

Phill Gross

